UID:YOlVabh55m0cZnITrrygC
SUMMARY:Seattle DSA Fundraising Drive
DTSTAMP:20260325T060838Z
DTSTART:20260405T130000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us on Sunday\\\, April 5th as we make calls to Seattle DSA
	 members and ask them to make monthly contributions to help close our $8\\
	\,500 budget gap this year! \\nSeattle DSA has been working hard this year
	 to protect our neighbors\\\, promote progressive taxes\\\, and fight for 
	a better world. Closing our budget gap will allow us to keep it up\\\, and
	 exceeding our goals would allow us to act even more boldly.  \\nYour frie
	nds and comrades are going to ask members who are currently giving monthly
	 local donations to chip in a bit more each month. We’ll also be calling m
	embers who aren’t yet providing donations to the chapter and asking them t
	o start.  \\nYou’ll be provided a script and a list of people to call. If 
	you’ve ever wondered how you can get people to buy into financially suppor
	ting grassroots projects\\\, this is a great place to start. \\nBeacon Hil
	l library branch\\nLocated right by Beacon Hill Link station\n\nhttps://se
	attledsa.org/event/seattle-dsa-fundraising-drive/\n\nFrom Seattle DSA
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/seattle-dsa-fundraising-drive/
LOCATION:Beacon Hill Branch – Seattle Public Library\\\, 2821 Beacon Ave S\
	\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98144\\\, United States
